Kanakapalli Anurag is an Andriod developer who graduated from the Kakatiya institute of technology. developed this app in MVVM architecture, using Kotlin. Created this app to help people who are gaining fat in this quarantine.

Ravi Anand Veludandi is from Warangal Urban, the second smartest city after Hyderabad in the Telangana state, India. He became the youngest IELTS, PTE and GMAT trainer in the city at an early age of 22.\n
Taught and brought up with the value of education and the elements that it held, Anand explored a lot of perspectives of it and has certifications and few diplomas from Harvard, MIT, University of California, Boston University, University of Birmingham, University of Toronto, Emory university, University of Texas system, Pennsylvania school of medicine, Amnesty International, Cambridge language assessment, British Council, Berklee college of music, Microsoft, Alison courses and few more in the fields of poetry, academic writing, functions of the human anatomy, physical education, entrepreneurship, art and music. Anand has an experience of more than 10 years in the fitness industry.

Going through many contemporary social media posts, urban Indian articles appears to be that most of the people are blessed with extra pounds of fat around their bellies, face, thighs, etc... The endless munching gives rise to weight gain Not everyone can afford expert nutritionist/dietitian to prepare a diet plan and I am one of them. This thing gave me the idea of losing these extra pounds of quarantine fat by developing an app for free to many. Mindless eating is the worst because you are consuming way too many calories without paying much attention. If you are working from home then you may be lost your daily routine, and also noticed that your eating habits have gone for a toss. This application diet plan is prepared with the help of many nutritionists, dietitians, and me
